node.text: Fridays are made for fish frys! You caught and cleaned your limit and now it's time to share the bounty. Hall of Fame angler @dalestroschein is in the kitchen with a fresh batch of walleye to show you how to fry them to perfection. #fishfryfriday

node.text: Nothing beats a fresh fish fry, but cleaning the fish properly can seem like a daunting task for some. Hall of Fame angler @dalestroschein has some tools and tips to make sure that you're getting as much meat as you can for the fryer! #walleyewednesday

Congratulations to the winners of the Bass Pro Shops US Open qualifying event at National Harbor, Md:

FIRST PLACE – Fishing buddies Duke Nave and Steve Allender from Oxford, Pa., and Rosedale, Md.
BIGGEST BASS/FAMILY TEAM – Father and son Leonard Switala and Lenny Switala from Pasadena, Md., and Georgetown, Del.
JUNIOR ANGLER – Father and son Iazarus Durham and Brandon Durham from Dumfries, Va.
HOMETOWN HERO/VETERAN – Fiances Christopher Schwartz and Darlene Jenkins from Cheltenham, Md., and Elkton, Md.

Thanks to everyone who braved the heat for a great day of fishing, fun, family and friends on the Potomac!
